message.content:
You can get Facebook credentials API to access the URL by implementing the following steps:

1. Create a Facebook Developer Account:
- Go to https://developers.facebook.com/ and sign in using your personal Facebook account.
- Complete the registration process if you haven't done this already.

2. Create a New App:
- Once logged in, click on "Create App" at the top right corner of the developers' dashboard.
- Choose an app type (For example: "For Everything Else").
- Fill out your app's display name and contact email, then select 'Create App ID.'

3. Set Up Products:
After creating your new app, you should be redirected to its Dashboard. Now,
- Click on "Set Up" next to 'Facebook Login.'
    
4.Submit Required Settings
Now you are inside the product settings for Facebook Login,
-Fill out “Valid OAuth redirect URIs”. It will look like “https://YOUR_PROJECT_ID.firebaseapp.com/__/auth/handler” replacing YOUR_PROJECT_ID with project-id which is visible at https://console.firebase.google.com/project/YOUR_APPLICATION/settings/
-Allow customers from anywhere but restricting them as per choice with countries option.
Click Save Changes

5.Get Essentials Credentials 
  To find credentials go back into developer homepage or simply follow Setting -> Basic settings where 
   -App-id :which was created while adding facebook-login product
   -Secret Key:o Obtain it click show button across App secret field followed by verification.

6.Task not yet over! You must submit development apps for review before they become open publicly [visible only when permission given].

Please note that continuously fetching APIs could lead frequentlying caps breaking & possible Suspected API keys.Please read through documentations linking terms of usage & best practices avoiding malfunction
